en_744907_0	Police Media Spokesman SP Ruwan Gunasekara has elaborated on the manner the voters should behave on the Election Day.
en_744907_1	The Police Media Spokesman said that based on the provisions in the Presidential Election Act certain activities are barred within a radius of 500 metres of the election booth, the day on which the election is being held.
en_744907_2	As an example he cited that propaganda activities have been banned.
en_744907_3	If already there is an election office legally established within this 500 metres, it is permitted to maintain any cutouts or banners legally established according to the guidelines.
en_744907_4	Other than that mass gatherings are barred in attrition to engaging in propaganda.
